<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>JARVIS Backup System — Documentation</title>
  <style>
    :root {
      --primary: #00ff88;
      --bg: #0a0a1a;
      --text: #e0e0e0;
      --muted: #888;
      --code-bg: #111;
      --border: #333;
    }
    * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
    body {
      font-family: 'Segoe UI', system-ui, sans-serif;
      background: var(--bg);
      color: var(--text);
      line-height: 1.6;
      max-width: 1000px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 2rem 1rem;
    }
    header {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 2rem 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }
    h1 {
      color: var(--primary);
      font-size: 2.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
    .subtitle {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 1.1rem;
    }
    nav {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 0.5rem;
      justify-content: center;
      margin: 2rem 0;
    }
    nav a {
      color: var(--primary);
      text-decoration: none;
      padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 4px;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
    }
    nav a:hover {
      background: rgba(0,255,136,0.1);
    }
    section {
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
      padding: 1.5rem;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02);
      border-radius: 8px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    h2 {
      color: var(--primary);
      margin-top: 0;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      font-size: 1.8rem;
    }
    h3 {
      color: var(--primary);
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      font-size: 1.3rem;
    }
    p { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    ul, ol { margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 1.5rem; }
    li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    code {
      background: var(--code-bg);
      padding: 0.2rem 0.4rem;
      border-radius: 3px;
      font-family: 'Consolas', monospace;
      font-size: 0.9em;
      color: var(--primary);
    }
    pre {
      background: var(--code-bg);
      padding: 1rem;
      border-radius: 6px;
      overflow-x: auto;
      margin: 1rem 0;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    pre code {
      color: var(--text);
      background: none;
      padding: 0;
    }
    .badge {
      display: inline-block;
      background: #222;
      color: var(--primary);
      padding: 0.2rem 0.6rem;
      border-radius: 4px;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      margin: 0.2rem;
    }
    .feature-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
      gap: 1rem;
      margin: 1rem 0;
    }
    .feature-card {
      background: rgba(0,255,136,0.05);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 6px;
      padding: 1rem;
    }
    .feature-card h4 {
      color: var(--primary);
      margin-top: 0;
    }
    .file-tree {
      background: var(--code-bg);
      padding: 1rem;
      border-radius: 6px;
      font-family: monospace;
      white-space: pre;
      margin: 1rem 0;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    footer {
      text-align: center;
      margin-top: 3rem;
      padding-top: 2rem;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 0.9rem;
    }
    @media (max-width: 600px) {
      body { padding: 1rem 0.5rem; }
      h1 { font-size: 1.8rem; }
      section { padding: 1rem; }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <h1>JARVIS Backup System</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Production-ready, git-based backup for your AI agent</p>
    <nav>
      <a href="#features">Features</a>
      <a href="#quickstart">Quick Start</a>
      <a href="#config">Config</a>
      <a href="#usage">Usage</a>
      <a href="#restore">Restore</a>
      <a href="#workflow">Workflow</a>
      <a href="#security">Security</a>
      <a href="/system-docs.html" class="text-primary">System Docs</a>
      <a href="/workflow.html" class="text-primary">System Workflow</a>
      <a href="/ai-updates-2025.html" class="text-primary">AI Updates 2025</a>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <section id="features">
    <h2>Features</h2>
    <div class="feature-grid">
      <div class="feature-card">
        <h4>Git Versioning</h4>
        <p>Every backup is a commit; full history with diff support.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <h4>Resource-Limited</h4>
        <p><code>nice</code> + <code>ionice</code> to avoid system load.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <h4>Locking</h4>
        <p>Prevents concurrent runs; safe for cron.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <h4>Compression</h4>
        <p>Gzip level 6 (adjustable 1-9).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <h4>Exclusions</h4>
        <p>Skip <code>node_modules</code>, logs, temp files.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <h4>Retention</h4>
        <p>Keep N days / N commits, auto-prune.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <h4>Encryption</h4>
        <p>Optional GPG encryption for sensitive data.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <h4>Notifications</h4>
        <p>Telegram & Slack alerts on success/failure.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="quickstart">
    <h2>Quick Start</h2>
    <p>Get backup running in 2 minutes.</p>
    <pre><code># 1. Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/amitvishwa19/getjarvisbackonline.git
cd getjarvisbackonline/fresh-backup-system

# 2. Edit config (set paths if needed)
nano config/backup.conf

# 3. Test configuration
./backup.sh --test

# 4. Run first backup
./backup.sh

# 5. Schedule daily (cron)
# crontab -e
0 2 * * * cd $(pwd) && ./backup.sh >> logs/backup-cron.log 2>&1</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section id="config">
    <h2>Configuration</h2>
    <p>Edit <code>config/backup.conf</code>. Key options:</p>
    <div class="file-tree">
BACKUP_PATHS="/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace"
BACKUP_REPO="./backup-repo"
RETENTION_DAYS=90
RETENTION_COUNT=365
COMPRESS_LEVEL=6
EXCLUDE_PATTERNS="backup-repo
node_modules
test-site
*.log
*.tmp
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db"
ENCRYPT=false
NOTIFY_TELEGRAM=false
LOG_LEVEL="info"
</div>
    <h3>Variables</h3>
    <table style="width:100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0;">
      <tr style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05);"><th style="text-align:left; padding:0.5rem;">Variable</th><th style="text-align:left; padding:0.5rem;">Required</th><th style="text-align:left; padding:0.5rem;">Default</th><th style="text-align:left; padding:0.5rem;">Description</th></tr>
      <tr><td style="padding:0.5rem; border-bottom:1px solid #333;">BACKUP_PATHS</td><td style="padding:0.5rem;">yes</td><td style="padding:0.5rem;">—</td><td style="padding:0.5rem;">Space-separated absolute paths</td></tr>
      <tr><td style="padding:0.5rem; border-bottom:1px solid #333;">BACKUP_REPO</td><td style="padding:0.5rem;">no</td><td style="padding:0.5rem;">./backup-repo</td><td style="padding:0.5rem;">Local git repo path</td></tr>
      <tr><td style="padding:0.5rem; border-bottom:1px solid #333;">RETENTION_DAYS</td><td style="padding:0.5rem;">no</td><td style="padding:0.5rem;">90</td><td style="padding:0.5rem;">Delete backups older than N days</td></tr>
      <tr><td style="padding:0.5rem; border-bottom:1px solid #333;">RETENTION_COUNT</td><td style="padding:0.5rem;">no</td><td style="padding:0.5rem;">365</td><td style="padding:0.5rem;">Keep at least N commits</td></tr>
      <tr><td style="padding:0.5rem; border-bottom:1px solid #333;">ENCRYPT</td><td style="padding:0.5rem;">no</td><td style="padding:0.5rem;">false</td><td style="padding:0.5rem;">Enable GPG encryption</td></tr>
      <tr><td style="padding:0.5rem; border-bottom:1px solid #333;">NOTIFY_TELEGRAM</td><td style="padding:0.5rem;">no</td><td style="padding:0.5rem;">false</td><td style="padding:0.5rem;">Send Telegram alerts</td></tr>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section id="usage">
    <h2>Usage</h2>
    <h3>Manual backup</h3>
    <pre><code>./backup.sh</code></pre>

    <h3>Test configuration</h3>
    <pre><code>./backup.sh --test</code></pre>

    <h3>Health check</h3>
    <pre><code>./scripts/health-backup.sh</code></pre>

    <h3>Schedule (cron)</h3>
    <pre><code># Edit crontab
crontab -e

# Add line:
0 2 * * * cd /path/to/backup-system && ./backup.sh >> logs/backup-cron.log 2>&1</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section id="restore">
    <h2>Restore</h2>
    <p>Recover any backup to a target directory.</p>
    <h3>1. Find commit hash</h3>
    <pre><code>cd backup-repo
git log --oneline</code></pre>
    <h3>2. Restore</h3>
    <pre><code>./scripts/restore.sh &lt;commit-hash&gt; /target/path</code></pre>
    <p>Example:</p>
    <pre><code>./scripts/restore.sh a1b2c3d /tmp/restore</code></pre>
    <p>All archives from that commit will be extracted into <code>/tmp/restore/&lt;archive-name&gt;/</code>.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="workflow">
    <h2>Workflow</h2>
    <p>Simplified backup flow:</p>
    <div class="file-tree">
┌────────────────────────┐
│ 1. Acquire lock        │ (prevents concurrent runs)
├────────────────────────┤
│ 2. Check deps          │ (git, tar, gzip)
├────────────────────────┤
│ 3. Init backup-repo    │ (if not exists)
├────────────────────────┤
│ 4. Archive each path   │ (nice/ionice, excludes)
├────────────────────────┤
│ 5. Git commit          │ (only if changes)
├────────────────────────┤
│ 6. Retention prune     │ (reflog expire + gc)
├────────────────────────┤
│ 7. Notify (optional)   │ (Telegram/Slack)
├────────────────────────┤
│ 8. Release lock & exit │
└────────────────────────┘
</div>
  </section>

  <section id="security">
    <h2>Security Notes</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Backup config may contain credentials; restrict file permissions (<code>chmod 600</code>).</li>
      <li>If using GPG encryption, back up your private key separately.</li>
      <li>Remote git pushes should use SSH keys, not passwords.</li>
      <li>The backup repository contains all your data — keep it secure.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <footer>
    <p>JARVIS Backup System v1.0 — Part of the JARVIS agent ecosystem</p>
    <p>MIT License</p>
    <p>Documentation generated: <span id="date"></span></p>
  </footer>

  <script>
    document.getElementById('date').textContent = new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0];
  </script>
</body>
</html>